.TH ISSEX 1 "2026" "issex" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
issex \- a lightweight file-based issue tracker
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B issex
.I command
.RI [ flags ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B issex
manages issues stored as Markdown files on disk.
Each issue lives in its own directory under a
.B notes/
folder, which is located by walking up from the current working directory until one is found (similar to how
.B git
locates a repository root).
Each issue directory contains a single
.B notes.md
file holding its metadata and free-form notes.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B add
Create a new issue.
.RS
.TP
.B \-name \fI<text>\fR
.RB ( required )
Short title for the issue.
.TP
.B \-priority \fI<n>\fR
Integer priority level. Defaults to
.BR 0 .
.TP
.B \-notes \fI<text>\fR
Free-form notes to embed in the issue file.
.RE
.TP
.B list
List issues, optionally filtered by a query expression (see
.BR QUERY\ SYNTAX
below).
.RS
.TP
.B \-src \fI<query>\fR
Filter expression. Omit to list all issues.
.RE
.TP
.B close
Mark an issue as CLOSED.
.RS
.TP
.B \-id \fI<huid>\fR
.RB ( required )
The HUID (human-readable unique ID) of the issue to close. HUIDs are printed by
.BR list .
.RE
.SH QUERY SYNTAX
Queries are small boolean expressions passed to
.BR list\ \-src .
Whitespace is ignored.
.PP
.SS Atoms
.TP
.BI p= n
Priority equals
.IR n .
.TP
.BI p> n
Priority greater than
.IR n .
.TP
.BI p< n
Priority less than
.IR n .
.TP
.B s=1
Status is OPEN.
.TP
.B s=0
Status is CLOSED.
.TP
.I huid_or_title
Match a specific issue by its HUID or title.
.SS Operators
.TP
.IB expr \ & \ expr
Logical AND (higher precedence than
.BR | ).
.TP
.IB expr \ | \ expr
Logical OR.
.TP
.BI ! expr
Logical NOT. Applies to the immediately following atom or parenthesised group.
.TP
.BI ( expr )
Grouping.
.SH EXAMPLES
Add an issue with priority 3:
.PP
.RS
.EX
issex add \-name "Fix segfault in parser" \-priority 3 \-notes "Happens on empty input"
.EE
.RE
.PP
List all issues:
.PP
.RS
.EX
issex list
.EE
.RE
.PP
List all open issues with priority greater than 1:
.PP
.RS
.EX
issex list \-src "p>1 & s=1"
.EE
.RE
.PP
List issues that are closed OR have priority 0:
.PP
.RS
.EX
issex list \-src "s=0 | p=0"
.EE
.RE
.PP
List all open issues that are
.I not
priority 5:
.PP
.RS
.EX
issex list \-src "s=1 & !p=5"
.EE
.RE
.PP
Close an issue by its HUID:
.PP
.RS
.EX
issex close \-id task_20260417_143022
.EE
.RE
.SH NOTES\ FILE\ FORMAT
Each issue is stored as a Markdown file with the following structure:
.PP
.RS
.EX
# <title>

\- ID: <huid>

## PRIORITY: <n>

## STATUS: OPEN|CLOSED

## NOTES:

<free\-form text>
.EE
.RE
.PP
The
.B HUID
is derived from the issue name and the creation timestamp
.RI ( name_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS ).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
No environment variables are used.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Missing required argument or invalid usage.
.TP
.B \-1
A command-level error occurred (e.g., issue not found, filesystem error, parse error).
.SH BUILDING
.B issex
ships with a self-rebuilding build script based on
.BR nob.h .
Compile the bootstrap once and it will keep itself up to date:
.PP
.RS
.EX
cc \-o nob nob.c && ./nob
.EE
.RE
.PP
This produces the
.B issex
binary (or
.B issex.exe
on Windows).
To enable Emacs-friendly output (file:line references), pass
.B \-DEMACS_PRINT
at compile time (already the default in
.BR nob.c ).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git (1),
.BR grep (1)
.SH BUGS
Report bugs by opening an issue with
.BR "issex add" .
